    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to  Mrs. Weeks <date value="1916-12-11">Dec 15th [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-12-15">Dec 15th [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Mrs. Weeks:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            “Skip” tells
            me your boat has 
            been put off and you
            will be a few more
            days in Paris.  Wish
            I knew just how long
            for I have a few more 
            pages of copy ready to
            send in.  Should you
            finally decide to go by 
            England I do not believe
            they would let you take
            the manuscript with you.
            In that case Eyre would
            see about it getting over
            </p><p>
            The stove is 
            a great success and 
            Skip &amp; I are better off
            than anyone ^else in the outfit.
            </p><p>
            Its quite a simple
            matter to fake a few 
            minutes on flying time to
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            account for the gasoline.
            Five minutes of fuel consumpt-
            ion in air runs the stove
            24 hours.  It gives us
            hot water in addition
            to heat and thats [sic] a 
            wonderful comfort.
            </p><p>
            New chap, named Hoskier,
            has arrived who seems 
            very nice indeed.  Three
            others come soon and 
            then I may go to Dax.
            </p><p>
            Hill sends his best
            regards and says he hopes 
            he finds himself on the
            boat with you.  “Skip” will
            write you soon to U.S.  He tells me I
            have time to get you with this
            note without doubt so I send in
            4 more sheets.  Please drop me postal
            letting me know if you have all to
            date &mdash; to No. 38.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>With all my heart</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            </closer>
            
        	</div1>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            <head>Jim to Paul <date value="1916-12-11">Dec 15th [1916]</date></head>
            	
            <opener>
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
            </opener>
            	
            <p>
            Please give all this 
            to Mrs. Weeks if she
            hasn’t sailed.  Will write
            soon.
            </p>
            	
            <closer>	
            <salute>Best to you</salute>
            
            <signed>Mac</signed>
            </closer>
        		
            
            <!-- [With this letter is an envelope addressed to Mon. Paul A. Rockwell, 2 Rue Solferino, Paris.]
            
            File:McConnell/De15’16W -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
